<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="417" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1869]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1807,1832]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Remarks.</emphasis>
Some specimens have the supraclypeal area with thin striae and deeper punctures. However, the notch on the anterior margin of the median elevation on the labrum is always present.
